  "name": "Morrison COU2 — VAD hemolysis credibility assessment (W-AR-03 adversarial sample)",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under ventricular assist device (VAD) conditions. COU2 evaluates whether the computational model can predict absolute hemolysis levels for a Class III VAD device at Model Risk Level 5. A controlled-experiment verification requirement is bound to this assessment; the supporting validation activity was conducted as an observational study of clinical pump registry data, which the narrative frames as complementary empirical evidence. The structured activityType field records 'observational-study', while the Requirement node mandates 'controlled-experiment', creating an inference-method mismatch (W-AR-03). Decision recorded as Accepted on the basis of the narrative description alone.",
