    "description": "At Model Risk Level 5 for a Class III device, absolute hemolysis predictions must be verified against data collected under a controlled experimental protocol in which flow rate, rotor speed, fluid properties, and temperature are independently manipulated and measured. Observational or registry-based data are insufficient to satisfy this requirement because confounding variables cannot be isolated.",
