      "type": "ValidationResult",
      "name": "VAD registry hemolysis observational comparison",
      "description": "Predicted hemolysis index values from the CFD model were compared against plasma-free haemoglobin measurements drawn from a retrospective clinical registry of 312 VAD implantations across three institutions. The registry data span the five target flow-speed operating points and provide a rich empirical basis for assessing model accuracy under real-world conditions. Agreement within ±18% was observed at four of five operating points, and the Monte Carlo uncertainty bands encompassed the registry median at all points. The breadth of patient variability captured in the registry is argued to provide stronger ecological validity than any single bench experiment. This result is cited as the primary empirical support for the hemolysis prediction claim.",
      "quantitativeMetric": "Mean absolute relative error 11.4% across 5 operating points; 95% Monte Carlo interval coverage 100%",
      "wasGeneratedBy": {
        "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/activity/vad-registry-observational-study",
