      "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/validation/monte-carlo-uq-result",
      "type": "ValidationResult",
      "name": "Monte Carlo uncertainty quantification on hemolysis predictions",
      "description": "A Monte Carlo UQ sweep (n=10,000 samples) was executed over the joint distribution of inlet flow rate (±5%), fluid viscosity (±8%), and power-law hemolysis model coefficients (±12%). The resulting 95% prediction interval for the normalised index of hemolysis (NIH) at the design operating point is [0.0031, 0.0058] g/100 L, which lies below the clinical threshold of 0.010 g/100 L with 99.2% probability. This UQ result satisfies the Monte Carlo requirement stated in the COU intendedUse.",
      "quantitativeMetric": "P(NIH < 0.010) = 0.992; 95% CI [0.0031, 0.0058] g/100 L",
