    "type": "DecisionRecord",
    "actor": "https://uofa.net/synth/actor/credibility-assessment-lead",
    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "The credibility assessment team concluded that the observational registry study, combined with Monte Carlo uncertainty quantification, provides sufficient empirical grounding for the hemolysis predictions. The registry encompasses 312 real-world VAD implantations spanning all five target operating points, and the 11.4% mean absolute error with full Monte Carlo interval coverage was judged to demonstrate adequate predictive accuracy. The team noted that the registry data offer ecological validity exceeding that of any single controlled bench experiment and that the Monte Carlo UQ satisfies the COU uncertainty quantification requirement. On this basis the package was accepted, with the recommendation that a controlled bench experiment be conducted prior to the next design iteration.",
